From cd54812f4f46291d4925d71399e9b07e7322d019 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: patch <patch@local>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 02:15:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: expand ship browser stat sorts (mobility, combat,
 mining)

- Add best-effort full-loadout stat sorts: boost speed, acceleration,
  agility, 100km/50km sprint time, total sustained DPS, volley damage,
  max weapon range, turret tracking, effective HP, shield regen, mining
  laser output, and a new 'Mining efficiency /100km' composite (cargo x
  mining output, discounted by round-trip travel time).
- bestEffortLoadout()/bestMiningLoadout(): greedy per-slot module pick
  (engines/shields by raw stat, weapons/turrets by sustained DPS, mining
  slots specifically preferring mining gear for the mining-focused
  sorts) so the browser can rank all 256 ships without a chosen role.
- Group the sort dropdown into General/Mobility/Combat/Mining optgroups
  now that it holds 16 stat entries instead of 5.

Fixes along the way:
- Bugfix: the roleSort auto-clear effect checked every roleSort value
  against availRoles only, so selecting any stat-based sort (all of
  which are never role ids) was immediately reset back to 'Sort: name'
  on the next render. Stat sorts now short-circuit past that check.
- Bugfix (engine/derive.ts): miningDPS summed burst/sustained across
  mining weapons, but every mining laser/drill in the dataset has both
  fields at 0 (their yield is modeled in  instead). This made
  miningDPS silently always 0 for every ship's real loadout, including
  the Fitting screen's 'Mining output' stat panel. Fixed to sum damage.
